secondary_street_name: adjacent to the East Coast Mainline
description: Redesign of Blocks HN1-4 as approved Outline planning permission under ref. P011501 on 30 May 2002 to now provide 164 affordable housing units along with offices (Class B1) at ground level and a Community Health Facility (Class D1) at ground and lower ground level with associated car parking and landscaping.
decision_conditions:
CONDITION:  No work shall be begun on the construction of any residential units until full details of a scheme for sound insulation have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details shall demonstrate how the residential units will achieve the indoor ambient noise levels specified in condition HW9, and will take into account reasonable ventilation requirements and the location of the particular building relative to potential noise sources including non-residential uses and traffic noises.

REASON:  In order to protect residential amenity.

Informatives
The following guidelines are recommended in terms of provision of ventilation. 
Dwellings falling within Noise Exposure Category B: Acoustic secondary glazed window capable of providing a staggered opening with indirect air route; or acoustically treated acoustic passive vents; or acoustically treated variable speed mechanical air supply unit with at least two specified settings. Dwellings falling within NECC or NECD: Acoustically treated acoustic passive vents; or acoustically treated variable speed mechanical air supply unit with at least two specified settings; or any other acoustically treated system of ventilation such as whole house ventilation approved by the Building Control Inspector.
